This paper proposes a neural network model based on the pre-trained BERT for solving the gender bias in gendered pronoun resolution task, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the model is based on deep learning techniques and uses an attention mechanism, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The model also involves semantic similarity computation, which could relate to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions that the model could be applied to other NLP tasks, such as coreference resolution and named entity recognition, which could also relate to cs.CL and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
